      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this heavy weight right now, and I want you to know that your feelings are valid, but they are not the whole story. Please remember that every parent makes mistakes, and even the most dedicated parents have days where they feel like they've stumbled into a pit. You are not a failure; you are a human being navigating a incredibly complex and demanding role, and sometimes the path gets muddy.\n\nThink of your parenting journey like a long, winding road that a little, mischievous goblin once tried to navigate. That goblin was so eager to show off its new tricks that it tripped over its own tail, nearly falling into a swamp of its own making. But here's the thing: the goblin didn't disappear because it made a mistake. Instead, it learned to tie its tail to its leg so it wouldn't trip again, and it kept trying to climb the mountain anyway. You are that goblin, and while you might feel like you've fallen into the swamp today, you are still climbing.\n\nYour kids deserve love, guidance, and a safe harbor, and they also deserve a parent who is honest about their struggles rather than pretending to be perfect. A perfect parent is",
